Here is an example SVG code for an ellipse with the text "+Add" centered in it:

```
<svg viewBox="0 0 100 50" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <ellipse cx="50" cy="25" rx="45" ry="20" fill="#fff" stroke="#000" stroke-width="2" />
  <text x="50" y="30" text-anchor="middle" alignment-baseline="central">+Add</text>
</svg>
```

In this example, the ellipse has a center point of (50,25), a horizontal radius of 45 and a vertical radius of 20. The `fill` attribute is set to white and the `stroke` attribute is set to black with a `stroke-width` of 2.

The text is positioned at the center of the ellipse using the `text-anchor` and `alignment-baseline` attributes. The `x` and `y` coordinates are set to 50 and 30 respectively, which correspond to the center point of the ellipse.

You can modify the SVG code to adjust the size and style of the ellipse and text to fit your specific needs.
